1.Text:
â€”And that wraps up the status of this year's
Halloween.

Within the private office of the Shadow Garden,
Alpha listens to Gamma's report and nods with
a satisfied expression.

I'm pleased to hear that it's been a tremendous
success. The Halloween event he suggested has
taken firm root in Midgar Kingdom.

Certainly. Mitsugoshi's branches have also achieved
impressive sales figures and established a solid
reputation.
Well then, what's with the long face?

...Huh? Oh, my apologies. It seems my emotions got
the best of me, and I've let them show...
What happened?

Actually...this year's Halloween has been even more
successful than anticipated, so we're currently
mobilizing all of our staff to handle the situation.

To be honest, it's been so well-received that we're
experiencing a shortage of staff for our pop-up
stores and branches...

I see. So we're already understaffed even at
this stage...

Yes. We're hastily making arrangements to provide
training for several individuals, including those
from the Garden's Numbers who seem promising,
with plans to dispatch them to different branches.

However, we've already received personnel requests
from our pop-up stores that can't wait until the
training is completed...
Is there really nobody available? No one at all?
Umm...
Gamma?
...Delta and Eta are still on hand.

Alpha prompts Gamma to continue her sentence, but she
freezes upon hearing the names she mentions.

(If we send those two, it could potentially increase
the workload at the store...)
Um...Lady Alpha?

Desperate times call for desperate measures. We need
to fill the personnel shortage.
*gasp* You mean...?!

Let's dispatch the two for a limited time and assign
them to specific, straightforward tasks until the
others have completed their training.
What?! Y-You can't be serious!
I am. We currently have no other option.

Alpha leans forward, rests her elbows on the table,
and instructs Gamma to summon the two.

Once Delta and Eta are summoned, Alpha proceeds to
explain the situation to them using clear and simple
language.

I have a single task to assign to both of you. Go to
the pop-up stores and give out sweets to the
children as part of the event.
Why do we have to give out candy?

It's not just about clearing excess inventory.
The goal is to boost sales at the main store
by giving out candy at the pop-up venues.
Boost...sales... Um, wha...?
Eta, you understand, right?

...The strategy is to lure customers with candy
samples...
What a relief. Yes, it seems you get the picture.
But...I can't stand...crowds...

Whether or not you can stand it, you have to do it.
You'll give sweets to children who say the words,
"Trick or Treat!"
Tri...ck?

Trick or treat. It means, "Give us candy, or we'll
play tricks on you."

What?! Only naughty children threaten others like
that! I'll take 'em all out!
Don't be silly! That's the way Halloween works.

Your job is to promote us to the children and their
guardians...creating opportunities for them to shop
at Mitsugoshi for future Halloweens.

So you must under no circumstances "take them all
out"!
Listening to you makes my head hurt, Gamma.
Whaâ€”?!
I can't stand...mobs of children...
Ugh! Eta!

Gamma turns away from Delta and Eta, facing Alpha
with a look of desperation.

Lady Alpha, sending these two to handle the job is
pointless... We should wait until the others finish
their training!

Grr... I may not get what you're saying, Gamma,
but I won't stand being made fun of by you!

Hm... If we don't have to go...then I agree with
Gamma...

We can't include anyone who lacks comprehension or
motivation as part of the workforce!
Quiet, all of you.

Alpha raises her hand to silence them, and all three
stop talking and freeze in their tracks.

Gamma, beggars can't be choosers. You underestimated
the situation and didn't make adequate preparations,
correct?

Y-Yes... My lenient judgment is largely responsible
for our current predicament...

Delta, your task is simple. Give sweets to children
as part of the pop-up store event.
Ha-ruff... I-I can do that...

Eta, take a moment to carefully consider the source
of your research funds. Now, answer me: Can I entrust
you with this job?
...And if I refuse?
You know what will happen, don't you?

My research funds will be reduced... Ack...
Understood...

After hearing the responses from the three, Alpha's
expression softens, and she claps her hands together.

I'm glad we've come to an agreement. Delta, Eta, head
to your destinations immediately.
Y-Yeah. Okay!
...Copy that.
Lady Alpha?

...I'd like to believe everything will be fine, but
Gamma, please ensure the others complete their
training as soon as possible.
Understood.

(I just hope pressuring them into this decision
wasn't a mistake...)

As Delta and Eta exit the room, Alpha gazes at the
door with a concerned expression on her face and
lets out a deep sigh.

2.Text:
W-Welcome. Thank you for coming. S-S-Such fine
weather we're having todayâ€”
Wetter?
...Skip the pleasantries. Just give us the details...
R-Right!

Face-to-face with two of the Shadow Garden's top
members, the pop-up store branch manager struggles to
maintain her composureâ€”her knees tremble nervously.

U-Um, I see you've already changed into your
costumes. Lady Delta, Lady Eta, we'd like for
you to go out into the city dressed like that.
I'm an super-smart witch!
...I'm a fluttery vampire...

The costumes suit both of you very well. Please try to
enjoy the Halloween festivities... I do apologize for
burdening you with such work. I feel terrible.

...Tell you what. I feel terrible about making you
feel terrible... We'll just leave...
No!

If we go back without doing anything, Lady Alpha will
be...really mad at us!
...Just thought I'd give it a try.

...We'll complete our mission properly. Tell us the
details...
Understood.

During the Halloween event, we'll be handing out
ribbons exclusively to children who have made
purchases at Mitsugoshi-affiliated stores.
Ribbons?

These ribbons come in three colors: red, blue, and
yellow, with each corresponding to the amount spent.
We would like you to give sweets to the children
based on the color of their ribbons.

When children approach, they will say, "Trick or
treat!" If a child's ribbon is red, please offer them
both cookies and candy; for blue ribbons, just
cookies; and for yellow ribbons, just candy.
Okay got it. Is that all?

Y-Yes... Once again, I'm terribly sorry, but can I
leave these tasks to you?
No problem! Leave it to me! I'll handle it just fine!

...Giving out different sweets based on the amount
spent? Trust Gamma to come up with such a messy
system...
Messy? I prefer a mess of cookies AND candy!
...Yeah, that's not quite what I meant.
Well, anyway, it'll be more of a mess to explain...
Alright, Eta! Off to the frontlines!
...What the heck?
It's something Boss man said before!
Hmm...

Watching the enthusiastic Delta exit the room, with
the somewhat reluctant Eta in tow, the branch manager
finally breathes a sigh of relief.

Delta and Eta venture out into the city carrying
baskets filled with sweets. There they immediately
find themselves surrounded by a throng of excited
childrenâ€”
Trick or treat! Give me sweets, witch lady!
Trick or treat! Me too! Gimme!
Hm?

Trick or treat! Hey, vampire lady! I've gotta red
ribbon!
Mine's blue... Oh, I forgot! Trick or treat!
Red. Got it. Blue. Here you go.
Hurry up, witch lady!
Umm... Red is this and this?
Hmm? And this one too?
Mine's yellow!
Yellow...is this and this? Oh, and this one!

Perhaps due to Eta's leisurely pace, most of the
children flock to Delta.
...Oh well.
U-Um... Trick or treat...
...A yellow ribbon. Candy... Here you go.
Th-Thanks! Bye, miss!
Bye...
Eta! What's taking you so long?
Heehee! I'm already out of sweets.
...Already?
I'll help you with yours, Eta!
...Sure. Thanks.
Leave it to me!

Eta hands her basket over to Delta. In no time at
all, the mountain of sweets rapidly vanishes.
Hee-hee-heeee! Finished!

Mission accomplished! Let's go report to that girl
from earlier! Hurry up, Eta!
Okay, okay...

Similar to when they entered the city, Eta quietly
follows behind Delta as she enthusiastically walks
ahead...

3.Text:
After giving out their sweets to the children, Delta
and Eta return and report to the branch manager.
However...

W-What's going on?! The amount of candy distributed
and the sales don't match up!
I distributed them properly.

...That's a lie. You got confused pretty early on
and handed out candy and cookies as a set to
everyone.
Grr! If you knew, you should've told me then!
...Too much of a hassle...

Argh! With all due respect! Please don't just pass
out sweets at random or ignore mistakes you're
well aware of! Take this seriously!
What's with the sudden attitude?

...Well, Gamma did pick her as the branch manager.
She might be the type who steps up when it really
matters.

Halloween isn't just about having fun! Please, for
this branch...and for the company's sake, lend us
your strength!

Seeing the branch manager's resolute expression
as she pleads desperately, Delta shifts her gaze
uncomfortably.
Argh... Fine! I'll do it!

...Not that I can picture you suddenly becoming
competent.
What'd you say?!
...Hold on a moment. I'll be right back...
Huh?! Where are you going?!
...To my lab.

With these words, Eta leaves the branch and makes her
way back to the Shadow Garden's hideout.
...So? Why did you come back here?

Eta is meant to be at the branch, but she returns
abruptly, leading to a confrontation with a puzzled
Gamma. Eta casts a fleeting glance at Gamma before
heading to her lab. However...
Wait! Explain yourself!
...I'm in a hurry...
*sigh* The branch manager is in trouble.
Huh?
So, I'm deploying a secret weapon.
A secret weapon?

Yes, it's for the branch manager. That's why I need
you to allocate me a budget.

Who's responsible for dispatching us two
troublemakers? That would be you, Gamma.
What?! Are you putting the blame on me?!
Own up to it.

...Alright, I'll do it. Just make sure to keep the
budget as low as possible!
Got it.

Eta holes herself up in her lab to craft a secret
weapon. Once it's completed, she returns to the
branch with it in tow...
Whoa... That's one big thingy you've got with you.
What in the world?

Facing Delta and the branch manager, Eta stands
proudly next to an object concealed beneath a cloth.

Ahem... Inspired by vending machines, Shadow Wisdom
taught to me by Master Shadow... I present to you...
Mr. Vendy the automatic dispenser!

Eta removes the cloth, unveiling Mr. Vendy, the
automatic dispenser, in all its glory.
Wh-Whoaaaa...!!! It looks kinda cool!

S-So this is...the Shadow Wisdom of Master Shadow,
said to be granted only to the chosen ones!

Eta! How do you make this thing work?! Hurry up and
tell me!

Well, seeing is believing...or something like that.
Let's see it in action.

Delta, Eta, and the branch manager head into the
city, bustling with Halloween spirit, to witness the
capabilities of Mr. Vendy, the automatic dispenser.

Eta sets up Mr. Vendy in the same spot where they
previously handed out sweets. After a while, a child
approaches...

What's this? It says to say the magic words...
*gulp* Tr-Trick or treat!

BEEP BEEP... BLUE RIBBON... THANK YOU FOR YOUR
PURCHASE OF OVER 5,000 ZENI, UP TO 10,000 ZENI.

With a clunk, a package containing cookies dispenses
from Mr. Vendy.
Wh-What the...?

The branch manager's expression stiffens upon
observing the mechanical response devoid of
humanity. However, Delta's eyes gleam.
N-No way! Even I won't mess this up!

...Forget messing up. We won't even need to do
anything.
Um, sorry, but do you really intend to use this?
...You've got a problem with that?

Concerned about the excessively impersonal exchange,
the branch manager cautiously asks Eta, who gestures
toward Mr. Vendy.
Whoa! What's this?! Cool!
I'm first! Wait your turn!

BEEP BEEP... BLUE RIBBON... THANK YOU FOR YOUR
PURCHASE OF OVER 5,000 ZENI, UP TO 10,000 ZENI.
Thank you, Mr. Vendy!
It seems super popular.

Everyone looks happy... I do less work... Is there a
problem?

Contrary to the branch manager's concerns, the
children lining up in front of Mr. Vendy are all
smiles.

Well... At the moment, it seems everything is fine.
Let's monitor the situation for now.
Yup... Problem solved.

Eta nods with satisfaction as she listens to Delta's
voice blending in with the delighted children.

4.Text:
BEEP BEEP... BLUE RIBBON... THANK YOU FOR YOUR
PURCHASE OF OVER 5,000 ZENI, UP TO 10,000 ZENI.
Thanks, Mr. Vendy!
Trick or treat!

BEEP BEEP... RED RIBBON... THANK YOU FOR YOUR
PURCHASE OF OVER 10,000 ZENI.
Th-Thanks...

The newly implemented Mr. Vendy distributes sweets
flawlessly without making any errors.
Delta and Eta are standing a short distance away.
Zzz...
Eta, Eta, wake up! I'm bored!
Zzz... Quiet... *snore*
I wanna do something fun! No sleeping!

...Ha-ruff... I said no sleeping... Don't you hear
me? I'm bored...

Delta finds herself with nothing to do, thanks to
Mr. Vendy's success. Suddenly, she catches wind
of an appetizing scent.
Something smells good... It's coming from over there!

Delta swiftly pivots her body and lunges toward the
source of the scent.
*drool*

Delta reaches an area lined with food stalls.
She comes to a halt in front of a particular
stall and wipes away drool from her mouth.
It looks and smells...delicious... *gulp*
Welcome! Step right up!
What is this?!

It's skewered chicken. This one's seasoned with salt
and grilled. That one's coated with a sweet and spicy
sauce.
*drool*

Judging by your appearance, you're from Mitsugoshi...
Would you like to buy some, young lady?
Can I?!
It'll be 300 Zeni per skewer.
Zeni?!
...I don't have any money...

If you don't have any cash on you, I can put it on
Mitsugoshi's tab.
Mitsugoshi's tab? I can buy it with that?
Yes, ma'am. So what'll it be?

Okay! Gimme the skewered chicken, one of each kind...
No! Five of each kind! Put it on Mitugoshi's tab!
Coming right up!

Delta's eyes sparkle with excitement as she holds
five skewers of chicken in each hand.

This tab thingy...! I don't really get it, but it's
incredible!
As long as I have this...!

Delta sinks her teeth into the skewered chicken.
She devours them quickly before rushing to the
next food stall she spots.

I'd like your limited-edition Halloween quiches!
Hmm...all types! Put it on Mitsugoshi's tab!
Of course. Coming right up!

Pumpkin soup? That's perfect for Halloween! Gimme a
large bowl! Put it on Mitsugoshi's tab!
Sure thing. Enjoy!

No need to slice the pumpkin pie! Just give me a
whole one! Put it on Mitsugoshi's tab!

Ghost pumpkin candles? Hmm... Put it on Mitsugoshi's
tab!
Mitsugoshi's tab!
Mitsugoshi's tab!!!

Delta goes on a shopping spree from stall to stall.
Before she knows it, her hands are full of Halloween
food and trinkets.
What else... Oh right!

I mean, it's Halloween, and there are so many rare
thingies. I'll get souvenirs for Boss man!

Candies, cookies, ghost pumpkin masks...and, and...
Oh! That looks cool as well!

With a radiant smile, Delta enthusiastically resumes
her exploration of the stalls.

5.Text: Trick or treat!

BEEP BEEP... RED RIBBON... THANK YOU FOR YOUR
PURCHASE OF OVER 10,000 ZENI.

Mr. Vendy, the automatic dispenser, distributes
sweets. However, the faces of the children who
receive the sweets seem...disappointed.
This Mr. Vendy is...kinda boring.

While receiving sweets is nice, the whole process
feels quite mechanical... I mean, it's impressive,
but is this really all that Mitsugoshi has to offer?

Mom, let's just get the sweets and check out a
different store!

The initial excitement diminishes as time passes,
and the children's enthusiasm wanes.

After returning from the food stalls, Delta blinks in
surprise at this scene.
Eta, Eta, wake up!
...I'm awake...
They're saying Mr. Vendy is boring.
Who...?
The kids. They're not interested anymore.
...But sweets aren't meant to be interesting...
...True.

Sweets aren't meant to be interesting...
just delicious!
...Are you done? I'm going back to sleep...

Don't you want some pumpkin soup? I went and bought
it for you!
...Mm... Later... Zzz...
She's asleep again. Grr... Fine, I'm off to playâ€”
U-Um, excuse me. Could I have a moment, please?!
Huh?

The nervous-looking branch manager appears before
Delta, who is about to take off, and the sleeping Eta.
Eta, the branch manager's here.
...Mmn... What...?
I think Mr. Vendy is incredible.

By instantly identifying the ribbon's color, it
accurately dispenses sweets without delay...
If we were to scale up production, it could
significantly reduce labor costs.
She's complimenting you, Eta.
Good to hear...
But!
But what?

While we can distribute the sweets properly using
Mr. Vendy, we cannot fully embody Mitsugoshi's
spirit of hospitality.
Hospitality? What's that?

Customer service techniques, or something like
that...

With Lady Gamma at the helm, Mitsugoshi's business
has been strategically managed until now. From coming
up with new products to distinguishing ourselves from
competitors...we've skillfully forged our way ahead.

Yet, despite our astute business practices, we've
also cherished genuine customer interactions. It
goes beyond mere customer service obligations.
We genuinely find it fulfilling.
Huh?

Delta and Eta exchange glances as the nervous branch
manager speaks passionately to them.
I don't really get it, but are we being scolded?

You find interacting with people fulfilling?
I'm struggling to get it...
Although I get we're being scolded...

Not fully grasping the meaning of the branch
manager's words, the two exchange puzzled
glances while feeling a slight sense of guilt.

6.Text:
After receiving a passionate lecture from the branch
manager about the essence of customer service, Delta
and Etaâ€™s next course of action isâ€”

The pumpkin pies taste different at different food
stalls! Some are sweet, and others are stuffed with
meat!

Lazing around in the hustle and bustle...is kinda
nice...
You eat too, Eta!
Mmph... Don't...force me...

Despite the branch manager's fervent speech, the two
continue enjoying Halloween without a care in the
world.
*sigh*
What's with the sigh? Aren't you gonna eat too?

Skewered chicken... I'm not in the mood to enjoy a
meal right now. Can't you two understand what I'm
trying to convey?
...Business is booming.
BEEP BEEP...BEEP...
...It'll reach its quota soon.
Huh?
...The sweets in Mr. Vendy are about to run out...

Oh, it's done already? Well, I'll head back to the
stalls then!
...I'm going home...

Ohh... Is it going to end like this? Mitsugoshi's
principles won't be properly conveyed to our
customers...

As the branch manager laments, a boy rushes up to
Mr. Vendy.
Trick or treat!
BEEP BEEP...BEEP... PSHHHT... OUT OF STOCK...
Oh... It's done.

It's run out of stock. Alright, I'll give that boy
his sweets, and we can wrap up this eventâ€”

But as the branch manager tries to approach the
boy...
Mr. Vendy's suddenly got...a different smell.
Huh?
OUT OF STOCK... RESTOCKING.

Mr. Vendy blares an error message, and its built-in
arms and legs start to move, snatching sweets from
children nearby.
Eeeek!
Whaâ€”?! What's going on?!
It's rampaging.

Now isn't the time for such calm remarks! If we don't
hurry up and stop it, the children might get hurt!
...Go on, Delta...
Jeez, fine. Be right back!
RESTOCKING... RESTOCKING...
Stop right there!

Delta leaps forward and kicks Mr. Vendy's extended
arm away from a girl holding sweets.
The crowd is kind of getting in Delta's way...
Ah! Everyone, please step back!

Mitsugoshi employees from the branch rush over,
guiding the public away from the scene.

Delta confronts Mr. Vendy head-on. Sensing this is no
time to be lazing around, Eta joins her.

Eta, what's going on? Why's Mr. Vendy acting so
weird?

...Well, I made it in a hurry, so the restocking
system is a bit sloppy...
...What's that supposed to mean?

It's an automated system for restocking sweets. But
the settings for where it restocks from... Well, you
get the picture.
I don't really get it!
...If you don't get it, that's fine.
Mr. Vendy is rampaging. Stop him.
I see! That's simple and easy to get!

With a wild grin on her face, Delta charges straight
at Mr. Vendy...
Whaâ€”?!

BEEP BEEP.. LOOTER IDENTIFIED. INITIATING
ELIMINATION PROTOCOL.

Mr. Vendy's arms and legs move swiftly, launching an
attack in an attempt to eliminate Delta.
Eta?! What the heck is this?!

...I thought enemies might come to steal the sweets,
so I equipped it with an armed security system...
...It's the perfect security system.
Security...system?

But it's only natural to protect food from enemies!
Well done, Eta!

This isn't a time for compliments! Why did you focus
on those features and neglect the restocking system?
...Personal tastes...?

Personal tastes...? Oh, Lady Delta! It's stealing
your food!
What'd you say?!

Delta turns around, only to find Mr. Vendy's extended
arms snatching the snacks and food she had procured.
Boss man's souvenirs...! I won't let you take 'em!
Eta! How do we stop Mr. Vendy?!

...There's an emergency shutdown switch. But it'll be
tough to press it while it's rampaging...

Then I'll make it stop moving! You do something in
the meantime!
...Talk about unscheduled labor...
Alright, here goes!

While Mr. Vendy continues its rampage, Delta
fearlessly leaps toward it. Eta looks for her
opening...

7.Text: Phew... I'm beat...
I'm not tired at all!

You're so weak, Eta, if just pressing a switch makes
you tired!
Okay, okay...

Mr. Vendy emits puffs of smoke and has completely
stopped functioning.
Hey, branch manager. We're done here, soâ€”

Delta turns towards where the branch manager is,
when...
Whoaaaaa!!! You ladies are amaaazing!!!

A wave of applause and cheers erupts from the crowd
evacuated by the Mitsugoshi branch's employees.
Wh-What the heck it this?!
No idea...
That was awesome, witch lady! You're super strong!
Thanks for protecting us! You looked really cool!

Mom! The witch lady and the vampire lady defeated the
bad Mr. Vendy!

Yes, that was incredible. I'm surprised by how much
of a show they put on.

Mitsugoshi always manages to impress. I can't believe
Mr. Vendy was part of this performance all along!
Performance...?
...The misunderstandings are escalating...

I thought you were weirdos giving out sweets...but
you're actually pretty amazing!
Thanks for getting our sweets back!
Witch lady, vampire lady, can I shake your hands?!
H-H-Hey... No pushing!
E-Eta! What's going on?!

...Don't know. There are a lot of people...
Wanna run?

No...running! I'm not sure, but I feel...nervous?
Excited? How about you, Eta?
Well...I don't feel bad...

Yup, yup. It's really something that they get how
awesome I am.

Eta and Delta find themselves surrounded by children
who gaze at them as if they are heroes.
Hey, witch lady! Trick or treat!
Hmm?
Me too! Miss Vampire! Trick or treat!
...Huh?

Hehehe. Witch lady and vampire lady, would you please
give out sweets to the children?

The two exchange glances as the branch manager smiles
and makes this request. Then...
Heehee! Well, since you insist, I'll do it!
...Oh well...
Okay, kids! Say the magic words!

Trick or treat! Give us candy, or we'll play tricks
on you!
Trick or treat!
Here you go...
Thank you, miss!
...Mm. You're welcome.

It's only after Eta and Delta finish handing out
sweets to the children that they realize they
both have smiles on their faces.
Lady Eta, Lady Delta, well done!

Despite the unfortunate trouble that occurred,
thanks to both of you, it didn't escalate into
a major incident. In fact, the Halloween event
was a great
success!

After giving out all the sweets, Eta and Delta return
to the Mitsugoshi branch.

Heehee! It's a piece of cake when I get serious
about it!

...Kids have way too much energy...but...well,
it wasn't not fun...

Umm... It wasn't not fun... Hmmm...oh! Which means it
was fun!

I had fun too! I think I sorta got what you were
saying!
Huh?
...That thing you said about customer service.

Ah... I'm really glad you were able to gain some
understanding of our philosophy at Mitsugoshi.
Thank you very much.
Halloween was such a great festival!

...Yeah. I'll prepare a more perfect Mr. Vendy for
next year...

With their work completed, satisfied smiles adorn the
faces of the witch and vampire.

That concludes the report submitted by the branch
manager regarding Eta and Delta's assistance at the
Mitsugoshi branch.

I was worried about how things would turn out,
but those girls really gave it their all.

Within the private office of the Shadow Garden,
Alpha listens to Gamma's report and nods with
a satisfied expression.

...Yes. We have successfully completed the training
for the new recruits. Eta and Delta are expected to
return tomorrow.

Then what's with the long face? I saw that same
expression on you just the other day.

...Please take a look at this. It's the report and
the balance sheet.
Let me see.

Here. Sales at Mitsugoshi's main store have been
strong this year, thanks to the events held in
various locations. The Halloween sales campaign
was a big success. However...
This is...a serious issue.

Alpha groans upon seeing the balance sheet, and
Gamma's expression is tinged with gloom...

The next day, after returning from the Mitsugoshi
branch, Eta and Delta visit Alpha's office to deliver
their report...
We're back! I did a perfect job!

...I've done a year's worth of work... I'll be holed
up in my research lab for a while...
We deserve to be rewarded...for ourâ€”
Eep?!
...I'm getting chills!

The two enter the office in high spirits, but they
come to an abrupt stop.

Welcome back. It seems you two had quite the
Halloween.
Wh-Why're you so angry?!
Take a look at this.
...The balance sheet...?

The Halloween sales campaign was a success, and sales
are up...but there's one problem. Take a look at the
expenses on the balance sheet.
Expenses?
Expenses...right...

Delta, these expenses on Mitsugoshi's tab are from
you, aren't they?

Mitsugoshi's tab! If you say those magic words at the
food stalls, you can get food without paying!

It's not "without paying." It means they trust
Mitsugoshi enough to postpone payment. 
And as for you, Eta...
...Mr. Vendy, huh...?

So, you're aware of it. How reassuring. What's the
deal with the massive production costs? They're
enough to offset the sales from the branch you
visited.
...But they were necessary expenses...

If I knew what "Mitsugoshi's tab" meant, I wouldn't
have done it! So...it's all the fault of the food stalls!

Sounds like you're making excuses... I wonder if
you're truly reflecting on your actions...
Eep?! Y-Yes, I am...
